value.title: Nikki Haley says Trump's post-election actions will be 'judged harshly by history'
value.excerpt: Former UN ambassador Nikki Haley distanced herself from her onetime boss, President Donald Trump, in a closed-door speech on Thursday night, telling members of the Republican National Committee that the President's actions after the election "will be judged harshly by history."

value.title: Why Trump's response to Capitol siege evokes memories of Charlottesville
value.excerpt: Trump groups violently stormed the U.S. Capitol, the surreal images took many back to a dark chapter when white supremacists openly descended upon Charlottesville.

value.title: Clyburn accuses resigning Trump Cabinet members of 'running away' from 25th Amendment duty
value.excerpt: House Majority Whip James Clyburn said former Trump Cabinet members Elaine Chao and Betsy DeVos, who resigned in protest of the Capitol riots, were "running away" from their responsibility to invoke the 25th Amendment.

value.title: Josh Hawley's ploy to be a pro-Trump hero results in withering blowback
value.excerpt: Missouri Sen. Josh Hawley offered pro-Trump demonstrators who stood outside the Capitol a raised fist salute as he walked into the Senate early on Wednesday, buoyant about his leading role in objecting to President Donald Trump's electoral defeat.

value.title: Colin Powell calls for Trump's resignation 'as quickly as possible': 'He should be totally ashamed of himself'
value.excerpt: Former U.S. State Secretary Colin Powell, a Republican, called for President Trump's resignation "as soon as possible."

value.title: Kurtz: 'No president has been able to dominate the media, social media, culture more than Trump'
value.excerpt: President Trump is one of the most influential presidents in United States history,” "Media Buzz" host Howard Kurtz said Friday.

value.title: Billionaire Trump supporters Catsimatidis, Olenicoff say he isn't to blame for US Capitol attack
value.excerpt: Few of Trump's billionaire donors have named the president in their public condemnations of the riots. Two actually say Trump didn't incite them.

value.title: Pelosi asks Joint Chiefs about preventing Trump from launching nukes
value.excerpt: House Speaker Nancy Pelosi spoke with the nation's top military officer on Friday about precautions in place to prevent President Donald Trump from ordering a nuclear strike or conducting other military hostilities as Democrats seek his removal from office.

value.title: POLITICO-Harvard poll: Public strongly backs Biden's demand for Covid aid
value.excerpt: There's strong public support for Biden's vision of an expansive government effort to combat the pandemic and its economic fallout.

value.excerpt: Former White House communications director Alyssa Farah criticized President Trump for his actions Wednesday amid the "heartbreaking" Capitol Hill riots that "crossed a line."

value.title: Trump says his supporters will still have a 'giant voice,' won't be 'disrespected'
value.excerpt: President Trump on Friday said his supporters will still have a “giant voice” and would not be “disrespected” after he leaves the White House.

value.title: With Merrick Garland pick, Biden signals stark contrast with Trump on Justice Department
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump declared nearly a year ago, "I am actually, I guess, the chief law enforcement officer," as he tried to assert control over Department of Justice decisions.

value.title: NBA: Los Angeles Lakers hope to meet President Joe Biden but champions lose at Spurs
value.excerpt: The Los Angeles Lakers hope to re-establish the tradition of NBA champions visiting the president of the United States.

value.title: Elaine Chao, Betsy DeVos step down from Trump Cabinet following Capitol storming
value.excerpt: Transportation Secretary Elaine Chao became the first Trump Cabinet member to resign in the wake of Wednesday's storming of the Capitol by the president's supporters.

value.title: Trump official merchandise stores removed by Shopify

value.title: Hear why Klobuchar fist-bumped Pence after Electoral certification

value.title: Trump's Education Secretary Betsy DeVos submits resignation
value.excerpt: Education Secretary Betsy DeVos has submitted her resignation, making her the second Cabinet member to resign over President Donald Trump's response to the mob breaching the US Capitol on Wednesday, according to an official.

value.title: 'Double standard': Biden, Black lawmakers and activists decry police response to attack on US Capitol
value.excerpt: Civil rights leaders blasted police for their response to an attack on the U.S. Capitol compared to clashes between Black Lives protesters and police.

value.title: Trump condemns 'heinous attack' on Capitol, calls for 'healing and reconciliation'
value.excerpt: President Trump condemned Wednesday’s “heinous attack” on the Capitol by his supporters and called for a moment of healing.
